		<pubDate>Mon, 16 Sep 2024 03:21:21 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid isPermaLink="false">/?post_type=work#038;p=88</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[This communication campaign focused on the problem of Heteronormativity in Vietnam. I and Ly had the chance to take on the art direction for the campaign. Following on the topic of Heteronormativity, we actually found out about this Heteronormative Design Discourse on Design Observer, which was kinda relevant and inspired us to dig further into [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
<html><body><p>This communication campaign focused on the problem of Heteronormativity in Vietnam. I and Ly had the chance to take on the art direction for the campaign. Following on the topic of Heteronormativity, we actually found out about this <a href="https://designobserver.com/feature/heteronormative-design-discourse/37940" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Heteronormative Design Discourse</a> on Design Observer, which was kinda relevant and inspired us to dig further into the discussion.</p>



<p>It addresses the often-overlooked matter of sexual identity within the design world and emphasizes the enduring prevalence of heteronormative assumptions in both design practice and discourse. The infrequent use of the term &ldquo;heteronormative&rdquo; in design discussions perpetuates a cultural norm that prioritizes heteronormative values and perspectives.</p>



<p>What we focused on were: unorthodox, marginalized, overlooked, underrepresented, non-canon, and radical.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image" style="--width:960; --height:712;"><img decoding="async" src="https://res.cloudinary.com/djtuan5jn/image/upload/v1697466986/personalwebsite/image/4a68d0c9-3c75-423e-b7db-7a6db94f36fa/cygu91lea92ihcahivo2.jpg" alt="hnh_01.jpg" width="960" height="712" fetchpriority="high"></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image" style="--width:2000; --height:1455;"><img decoding="async" src="https://res.cloudinary.com/djtuan5jn/image/upload/v1697466993/personalwebsite/image/4a68d0c9-3c75-423e-b7db-7a6db94f36fa/sjqh2fzejkun909kagme.jpg" alt="hnh_03.jpg" width="2000" height="1455" fetchpriority="high"></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image" style="--width:2000; --height:1388;"><img decoding="async" src="" alt="hnh_06.jpg" width="2000" height="1388" data-src="https://res.cloudinary.com/djtuan5jn/image/upload/v1697467003/personalwebsite/image/4a68d0c9-3c75-423e-b7db-7a6db94f36fa/la5wuhg7skuhhf6maryx.jpg" data-srcset="" srcset=""></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image" style="--width:2000; --height:2000;"><img decoding="async" src="" alt="Copy_of_engage01_-_paper_plane_Song_Lang.jpg" width="2000" height="2000" data-src="https://res.cloudinary.com/djtuan5jn/image/upload/v1697467010/personalwebsite/image/4a68d0c9-3c75-423e-b7db-7a6db94f36fa/vy66za5upj2l1fpvxrrc.jpg" data-srcset="" srcset=""></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image" style="--width:2000; --height:2000;"><img decoding="async" src="" alt="vn_mimnh3.jpg" width="2000" height="2000" data-src="https://res.cloudinary.com/djtuan5jn/image/upload/v1697467017/personalwebsite/image/4a68d0c9-3c75-423e-b7db-7a6db94f36fa/mkhz6y4eopz2ufs6s62b.jpg" data-srcset="" srcset=""></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image" style="--width:2000; --height:2000;"><img decoding="async" src="" alt="Copy_of_engage01_-_paper_plane_CMBYN.jpg" width="2000" height="2000" data-src="https://res.cloudinary.com/djtuan5jn/image/upload/v1697467023/personalwebsite/image/4a68d0c9-3c75-423e-b7db-7a6db94f36fa/ctdgefgfxhdxzsjklnmd.jpg" data-srcset="" srcset=""></figure>



<p>Here are my motion graphic designs for the campaign. The typography revolved around the shapes and silhouettes of everyday objects in Vietnam, such as plastic stools or household stand fans.</p>



