										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
<html><body><p>This is an entry for the Google Development Solution Challenge, which involves UI/UX design and visual development for a smartphone app designed to facilitate the buying and selling of used goods.</p>



<p>The app is tailored specifically for students and residents of the Vietnamese National University village, where most of the team&rsquo;s member live. Given that many college students in this area have limited expenditure and rely on the second-hand &amp; giveaway economy, the app aims to provide a convenient mobile platform for their needs, ranging from clothes, books to more valuable items like household appliances or motorbikes.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo span2"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
